{"cursor":"52021","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox officeholder |name = Kofi Annan |image = Kofi Annan.jpg |office = Secretary-\nGeneral of the United Nations |deputy = Louise FrÃ©chette Mark Malloch Brown\n|term_start = 1 January 1997 |term_end = 31 December 2006 |predecessor = Boutros\nBoutros-Ghali |successor = Ban Ki-moon |office1 = United Nations and Arab League\nEnvoy to Syria\n|1blankname1 = 1namedata1 = Ban Ki-moon (UN) Nabil Elaraby (AL)\n|term_start1 = 23 February 2012 |term_end1 = 31 August 2012 |predecessor1 =\nPosition established |successor1 = Lakhdar Brahimi |birth_date = |birth_place =\nComassie, Gold Coast (now Kumasi, Ghana) |death_date =\n|death_place = |spouse = Titi Alakija (1965âlate 1970s) Nane\nLagergren (1984âpresent)\n| relations = Anthony Gildas Kofi Annan\n|children = Kojo Ama Nina |alma_mater = Kwame Nkrumah University of\nScience and Technology Macalester College Graduate Institute of\nInternational and Development Studies Massachusetts Institute of Technology\n|religion = Protestantism |signature = KofiAnnan.jpg }} 'Kofi Atta\nAnnan' (; born 8 April 1938) is a Ghanaian diplomat who served as the seventh\nSecretary-General of the United Nations, from 1 January 1997 to 31 December\n2006. Annan and the United Nations were the co-recipients of the 2001 Nobel\nPeace Prize for his founding of the Global AIDS and Health Fund to support\ndeveloping countries in their struggle to care for their people.\n\nFrom 23 February until 31 August 2012, Annan was the UNâArab League Joint\nSpecial Representative for [http://www.un.org/wcm/content/site/undpa/main/activ-\nities_by_region/middle_east/syria] Syria, to help find a resolution to ongoing\nconflict there. BBC News. 23 February 2012[http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-\n17144805 \"Syria faces ultimatum from international conference.\"] Annan\nquit after becoming frustrated with the UN's lack of progress with regard to\nconflict resolution, {{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/Kofi-Annan-\nresigns-as-UN-Syria-envoy/articleshow/15329904.cms|title= Kofi Annan resigns as\nUN Syria envoy |accessdate=2 August 2012}} stating that \"when the Syrian\npeople desperately need action, there continues to be finger-pointing and name-\ncalling in the Security Council.\"\n","linknr":1001,"url":"Kofi_Annan","recorded":1362674550,"links":146,"instances":["former_french_degree","british_colony","class"],"pdf":["http://www.amacad.org/publications/BookofMembers/ChapterA.pdf","http://www.amacad.org/publications/BookofMembers/ChapterA.pdf","http://www.zypern.cc/extras/annan-plan-for-cyprus-2004.pdf"],"categories":["1938 births","Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology alumni","Mfantsipim School alumni","Fellows of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences","Ghanaian diplomats","Ghanaian economists","Ghanaian Nobel laureates","Ghanaian politicians","Ghanaian Protestants","Humanitarians","Living people","Macalester College alumni","Massachusetts Institute of Technology alumni","MIT Sloan Fellows","MIT Sloan School of Management alumni","Nobel Peace Prize laureates","Olof Palme Prize laureates","Recipients of the Gottlieb Duttweiler Prize","Recipients of the Indira Gandhi Peace Prize","The Elders (organization)","United Nations Oil-for-Food scandal","United Nations Secretaries-General","Grand Collars of the Order of Liberty","Grand Crosses of the Order of Merit of the Federal Republic of Germany","Honorary Knights Grand Cross of the Order of St Michael and St George","Knights Grand Cross of the Order of the Netherlands Lion","Companions of the Order of the Star of Ghana","Sashes of the Order of the Star of Romania","Chiefs of the Order of the Golden Heart of Kenya","Recipients of the Grand Decoration with Sash for Services to the Republic of Austria"],"headings":["Early years and education","Early career","Secretary-General of the United Nations","Recommendations for UN reform","Post-UN career","Per